Goal/spec: {goal}
Target Widget Blueprint: {asset_path}
Reference screen size: {screen_size}
Style notes: {style_notes}
Constraints: {constraints}

Convert the spec into an executable MCP workflow. Prefer this order: inspect-widget-blueprint when editing an existing asset, create-widget-blueprint when the asset is new, edit-widget-blueprint for batched widget tree/property/slot operations, edit-widget-layout-batch only for layout-only passes, and inspect-widget-blueprint again for verification. Include dry_run=true before destructive or broad writes, then compile/save policy for the final call. Return concrete planned tool calls with JSON-shaped arguments, including widget names, parent widgets, widget classes, and slot data where the spec gives enough detail. Call out missing details as assumptions rather than adding unsupported behavior.
